CRISPR-Tools Sales Agent Design
High-Level Architecture

Single Sales Agent implementing two subroutines:

Lead Finding Agent – discovers and validates new leads.

Lead Emailing Agent – drafts, verifies, and sends cold emails.

Designed to run weekly:

~50 new target customers emailed per week.

~50–100 model prompts per week (batched for efficiency).

Core Components
Component	Choice for Free/Effective Use
Model	GPT‑4o-mini (OpenAI free-tier via ChatGPT or free API credits) for lead evaluation, relevance scoring, and email drafting.
Optionally: Claude Instant Free or Gemini/Bard free tier for web search and summarization.
Tools	Google Sheets – memory / CRM, free.
Gmail (separate contact@crispr-tools.com
) – email sending.
Hunter.io free tier – email discovery.
MailTester / free verification tool – validate emails.
Requests + BeautifulSoup – scrape About/Contact pages.
Instructions	Detailed prompt instructions for:
- Finding relevant researchers.
- Filtering by target fit.
- Drafting personalized cold emails.
- Formatting output as JSON for Sheets.
Guardrails	- Ensure email is professional, polite, safe, and spam-free.
- Max 120–150 words per email.
- Use personalization (name, organization, role).
- Avoid sensitive or inappropriate content.
Lead Finding Agent Routine

Web/Research Prompting

GPT‑4o-mini + Gemini/Bard or Claude Instant:

“Find 50 gene editing researchers or professionals in academia, biotech, and startups relevant to CRISPR.”

Output structured as JSON: Name | Org | Role | Status=ready.

Lead Verification

Prompt GPT-4o-mini to score leads on relevance (“Would this person find https://www.crispr-tools.com
 useful?”).

Email Discovery

Use Hunter.io free tier for public email search.

Fallback: scrape organization websites (About/Contact pages) using requests + BeautifulSoup.

Generate naive guesses: first.last@org.com if necessary.

Email Validation

Verify using MailTester or similar free tools.

CRM / Memory

Add leads to Google Sheets with columns:
Name | Org | Role | Email | Status (Status=ready).

Lead Emailing Agent Routine

Identify Leads Not Emailed

Filter Google Sheet where Status=ready.

Draft Personalized Emails

Prompt GPT‑4o-mini to generate a 120-word email per lead:

Include Name, Org, Role.

Introduce CRISPR-Tools as free directory.

Output as plain text.

Guardrails

Verify emails are professional, polite, safe.

Optionally prompt GPT-4o-mini with:

“Check this email and return OK if safe and professional, else rewrite.”

Send Emails

Use Gmail API / Google Apps Script to send in small batches from contact@crispr-tools.com.

Respect Gmail limits (100/day free, 500/day Workspace).

Update Sheet

Mark Status=sent.

Back-of-the-Envelope Scaling
Metric	Estimate
Leads added weekly	50–100
Emails sent weekly	50
Model prompts	50–100 (batched in chunks of 5–10 leads per prompt)
Tools / free-tier limits	Gmail: 100/day, Hunter.io: 25 searches/mo, GPT‑4o-mini: free ChatGPT or free API credits
Implementation Notes / Free Optimization

Batching: Feed 5–10 leads per prompt to GPT to save tokens.

Hybrid Search: Use Gemini/Bard free-tier for live web research; feed results to GPT‑4o-mini for extraction.

Email Safety: Always run guardrail prompt before sending.

Separate email account: Keep your personal Gmail safe, use contact@crispr-tools.com.

Error handling: Skip leads with invalid emails or duplicates in Sheets.

Manual fallback: Small-scale scraping + model filtering allows you to run everything without paying for APIs, staying within free-tier limits.

This design maximizes free usage while being effective, safe, and automatable.

